data.enText: leapt
leapt
or
leaped
leaped

data.chText: 跳；跳跃；跳越
data.enText: to jump high or a long way

data.chText: 海豚跃出水面。
data.enText: A dolphin leapt out of the water.

data.chText: 我们跳过了那条小溪。
data.enText: We leapt over the stream.

data.chText: 那匹马跃过了一道五英尺高的墙。
data.enText: The horse leapt a five-foot wall.

data.chText: 猛冲；突然做（某事）
data.enText: to move or do sth suddenly and quickly

data.chText: 她突然翻身下了床。
data.enText: She leapt out of bed.

data.chText: 他冲过房间去开门。
data.enText: He leapt across the room to answer the door.

data.chText: 我赶紧站了起来。
data.enText: I leapt to my feet (= stood up quickly) .

data.chText: 他们立即断然采取了行动。
data.enText: They leapt into action immediately.

data.chText: 她马上挺身而出为我辩护。
data.enText: She was quick to leap to my defence (= speak in support of me) .

data.chText: 那张照片跃然纸上，引人注目。
data.enText: The photo seemed to leap off the page (= it got your attention immediately) .

data.chText: 他的名字一下引起了我的注意。
data.enText: His name leapt out at me (= I saw it immediately) .

data.chText: 骤增；剧增；猛涨
data.enText: to increase suddenly and by a large amount

data.chText: 股价从476便士猛涨到收盘536便士。
data.enText: Shares leapt in value from 476p to close at 536p.
look before you leap

data.chText: 三思而后行
data.enText: used to advise sb to think about the possible results or dangers of sth before doing it
jump/leap to conclusions
jump/leap to the conclusion that…

data.chText: 匆忙下结论；贸然断定
data.enText: to make a decision about sb/sth too quickly, before you know or have thought about all the facts

data.chText: 我又犯老毛病了，冒冒失失地就下结论。
data.enText: There I go again─jumping to conclusions.
leap at sth

data.chText: 赶紧抓住，急不可待地接受（机会）
data.enText: to accept a chance or an opportunity quickly and with enthusiasm

data.chText: 我立刻抓住了去法国的机会。
data.enText: I leapt at the chance to go to France.

data.chText: 跳越；跳跃；跳高
data.enText: a long or high jump

data.chText: 一跳跳了六米
data.enText: a leap of six metres

data.chText: 她一个飞跃跳到小溪的对面。
data.enText: She took a flying leap and landed on the other side of the stream.

data.chText: 他看见她时，心猛地一跳。
data.enText: His heart gave a sudden leap when he saw her.

data.chText: 从电视业转向电影业很少有人成功。
data.enText: Few people successfully make the leap from television to the movies.

data.chText: 骤变；剧增；激增
data.enText: a sudden large change or increase in sth

data.chText: 利润跃升
data.enText: a leap in profits
by/in leaps and bounds

data.chText: 非常迅速；飞跃地；突飞猛进；大量地
data.enText: very quickly; in large amounts

data.chText: 她的健康已迅速好转。
data.enText: Her health has improved in leaps and bounds.
a leap in the dark

data.chText: （未了解情况就采取的）冒险举动
data.enText: an action or a risk that you take without knowing anything about the activity or what the result will be

ex.chText: 他从三楼的窗户跳了下来。
ex.enText: He jumped out of a third-storey window.

ex.chText: 他一下子跳了起来，跑出了房间。
ex.enText: He jumped to his feet and ran out of the room.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指用双脚向上、向下跳，或跳到、跳过一定距离外的某一点。

ex.chText: 他跃过围栏，跑向电影院。
ex.enText: He leapt/jumped the fence and ran to the cinema.

ex.chText: 一条鱼跃出水面落到岸上。
ex.enText: A fish leapt/jumped out of water and landed on the shore.

synonyms.bx: 常可与 jump 换用，但侧重表示身体猛力向上跃起并朝前急冲的动作，有时含突然之意。

ex.enText: The cat sprang out of the door.
He sprang to his feet and ran downstairs.

synonyms.bx: 指凭借很强的弹跳力突然而快速地跳跃。

ex.zh: 纵身一跃；发生飞跃性变化
巨大的跳跃；巨大的增长

tr: a light, self-propelled movement upwards or forwards
the distance leaped (or to be leaped)

example: a successful leap from college to the major leagues

tr: pass abruptly from one state or topic to another
example: jump from one thing to another

tr: move forward by leaps and bounds
example: The horse bounded across the meadow
The child leapt across the puddle
Can you jump over the fence?
the trainer jumped the tiger through the hoop

tr: jump down from an elevated point
example: the parachutist didn't want to jump
every year, hundreds of people jump off the Golden Gate bridge
the widow leapt into the funeral pyre

value.boxr_value: British English usually uses the form leapt as the past tense and past participle. American English usually uses leaped. 英国英语通常用leapt作过去式和过去分词，美国英语则通常用leaped。

value.def: If you leap, you jump high in the air or jump a long distance.

example.ex: He had leapt from a window in the building and escaped...
example.tran: 他从大楼一个窗口跳出去跑了。

example.ex: The newsreels show him leaping into the air...
example.tran: 新闻短片里有他跳向空中的画面。

example.ex: The man threw his arms out as he leapt.
example.tran: 该男子张开双臂，纵身一跳。

example.ex: Smith took Britain's  fifth medal of the championships with a leap of 2.37 metres.
example.tran: 史密斯跳出2.37米的成绩，为英国夺得锦标赛的第5枚奖牌。

value.def: If you leap somewhere, you move there suddenly and quickly.

example.ex: The two men leaped into the jeep and roared off...
example.tran: 两名男子跳上吉普车，疾驰而去。

example.ex: With a terrible howl, he leapt forward and threw himself into the water.
example.tran: 他狂吼一声，向前猛冲，纵身跳进水中。

value.def: If a vehicle leaps somewhere, it moves there in a short sudden movement.
A leap is a large and important change, increase, or advance.

example.ex: The result has been a giant leap in productivity.
example.tran: 其结果是生产力的大幅提高。

example.ex: ...the leap in the unemployed from 35,000 to 75,000...
Contemporary art has taken a huge leap forward in the last five or six years.
example.tran: 当代艺术在过去五六年间突飞猛进。

value.def: If you leap to a particular place or position, you make a large and important change, increase, or advance.

example.ex: Warwicks leap to third in the table, 31 points behind leaders Essex.
example.tran: 沃里克队在排名中蹿升至第3名，落后领先的埃塞克斯队31分。

value.def: If you say that your heart leaps, you mean that you experience a sudden, very strong feeling of surprise, fear, or happiness.

example.ex: My heart leaped at the sight of her.
example.tran: 我见到她时心都要跳出来了。

value.tran: （因吃惊、害怕、高兴等心脏）猛地跳动

value.def: If you leap at a chance or opportunity, you accept it quickly and eagerly.

example.ex: The post of principal of the theatre school became vacant and he leapt at the chance.
example.tran: 戏剧学校校长一职出缺，他马上抓住了这个机会。

value.def: You can use in leaps and bounds or by leaps and bounds to emphasize that someone or something is improving or increasing quickly and greatly.

example.ex: He's improved in leaps and bounds this season...
example.tran: 他今季的表现一日千里。

example.ex: The total number of species on the planet appears to be growing by leaps and bounds.
example.tran: 地球上的物种数目似乎正飞速增长。

value.tran: （改善或增长）非常迅速地，飞跃地

value.def: If you take a leap in the dark or a leap into the unknown, you do something without having any previous experience in that activity or knowledge of it.

example.ex: Prudent people are not going to take a leap in the dark...
example.tran: 小心谨慎的人是不会轻易冒险的。

example.ex: Once more he's making a leap into the unknown without a plan.
example.tran: 他再次毫无计划地乱闯。

trans: （改善或增长）非常迅速地，飞跃地
